---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AttributionBadge from '../components/AttributionBadge.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About 944 Hub — the open-source Porsche 944 repair manual.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-extrabold text-ink">About 944 Hub</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
      944 Hub is a free, open-source repair and knowledge platform for the Porsche 944, 944 Turbo,
      924S and 968 — inspired by classic resources like
      <a href="https://www.clarks-garage.com" class="font-semibold text-guards hover:underline">Clark's Garage</a>
      and rebuilt for modern accessibility, search and community collaboration.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl font-bold text-ink">Our mission</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-soft">
      To become the definitive open-source knowledge base for the Porsche 944 — preserving proven
      knowledge while enabling modern contributions and continuous improvement. Nothing behind a
      paywall, nothing locked in a forum thread that disappears next year.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl font-bold text-ink">How content is credited</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-soft">Every article carries a small red mark identifying its source, so original authors always get credit:</p>
    <ul class="mt-5 space-y-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <AttributionBadge author="CG" size="md" />
        <span class="text-ink-soft"><strong class="text-ink">Clark's Garage (CG)</strong> — legacy reference material, ported here with attribution and a link back to the original.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <AttributionBadge author="FFP" size="md" />
        <span class="text-ink-soft"><strong class="text-ink">FormFactor Performance (FFP)</strong> — original content, upgrades and performance write-ups from our sponsor.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <AttributionBadge author="community" size="md" />
        <span class="text-ink-soft"><strong class="text-ink">Community (CC)</strong> — contributions from 944 owners, credited individually where applicable.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ── In memory of Clark Fletcher ──────────────────── -->
    <div class="mt-12 rounded-xl border border-brick/30 bg-brick/[0.06] p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="rounded-sm bg-brick px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-[0.62rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white">In memory</span>
        <span class="font-mono text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-soft/60">d. Fall 2017</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-2xl font-bold text-ink">Clark Fletcher</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ink-soft">
        Clark's Garage was the work of one man. Driven by his love for the Porsche 944, Clark Fletcher
        single-handedly built one of the most thorough 944 repair resources ever put online — and gave
        it away freely to anyone who needed it. Clark passed away in the fall of 2017.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ink-soft">
        The knowledge he gathered has kept countless 944s on the road, and it forms the foundation of
        everything here. We're deeply grateful to Clark, and to his family, for allowing his work to live
        on. 944 Hub exists to carry that spirit forward — knowledge shared freely, for every 944 owner who
        comes next. Rest easy, Clark.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl font-bold text-ink">Other good sources</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-soft">
      944 Hub is one stop, not the only one. For real-time help, second opinions and a deep well of
      collective experience, these communities are worth your time:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-ink-soft">
      <li>
        <a href={SITE.discord} class="font-semibold text-guards hover:underline">Porsche Transaxle Discord</a>
        — an active community of 944, 924, 928 and 968 owners sharing diagnostics, build threads and
        live wrenching advice.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.clarks-garage.com" class="font-semibold text-guards hover:underline">Clark's Garage</a>
        — the foundational reference much of the legacy material here is ported from.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="mt-12 rounded-xl border border-line bg-surface p-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-ink">Sponsored by {SITE.sponsor.name}</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-soft">
        944 Hub is proudly sponsored by {SITE.sponsor.name}. The platform is free and open source — the code
        under the MIT license and the content under CC BY-SA 4.0.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div id="affiliate-disclosure" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 rounded-lg border border-line bg-surface p-5 text-sm text-ink-soft">
      <strong class="text-ink">Affiliate disclosure.</strong> {SITE.affiliate.full}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 rounded-lg border border-line bg-surface p-5 text-sm text-ink-soft">
      <strong class="text-ink">A note on Clark's Garage.</strong> The legacy material here is preserved out of
      respect for Clark's work and for a foundational community resource. Every ported article links back to its
      original page. If you are a rights holder and would like a change, please reach out via our
      <a href={SITE.github} class="font-semibold text-guards hover:underline">GitHub repository</a>.
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
